<div id="review_4296046403" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4296046403" />
    <a title="Corey Woodcock" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/75181598-corey-woodcock"><img alt="Corey Woodcock" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1628649921p2/75181598.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4296046403?book_show_action=true">Dec 21, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Corey Woodcock" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Corey Woodcock" href="/user/show/75181598-corey-woodcock">Corey Woodcock</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780312952716" href="/book/show/606991.A_Simple_Plan">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4296046403" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15028346629580205005"><i>
  <b>”It’s like those old stories about people selling their souls. I did one bad thing, and it led to a worse thing, and on and on and on, until I finally ended up here. This is the bottom…”</b>
</i><br/><br/>Two brothers and a friend stumble across a downed plane in the middle of a snowy wilderness, and inside the plane next to the dead pilot is a duffel bag containing 4.5 million dollars. Nobody knows about the wreck and it likely won’t be discovered until the snow melts in the spring. Of course, they decide to </span>
  <span id="freeText15028346629580205005" style="display:none"><i>
  <b>”It’s like those old stories about people selling their souls. I did one bad thing, and it led to a worse thing, and on and on and on, until I finally ended up here. This is the bottom…”</b>
</i><br /><br />Two brothers and a friend stumble across a downed plane in the middle of a snowy wilderness, and inside the plane next to the dead pilot is a duffel bag containing 4.5 million dollars. Nobody knows about the wreck and it likely won’t be discovered until the snow melts in the spring. Of course, they decide to take the money and split it, but under one strict condition: if anything begins to go wrong, they burn the money and forget the whole thing ever happened. “A simple plan”, right? What could possibly go wrong?<br /><br />This is my first Scott Smith novel, a vicious and brutal journey into the depths of depravity as we follow the three main characters on their journey to keep the money. Motivation? Pure greed and not getting caught. It’s probably worse than you think. Smith’s writing is fast and furious, and he spares no expense. He wants to make you uncomfortable by pulling up the sheet on human nature at its absolute worst, and I’d say he succeeds at this.<br /><br />I’m giving this book four stars, but I did teeter back and forth between four and four and half; ultimately I went with four because when it comes right down to it, this was quite an unpleasant book to read, with not a single likable main character. It was tough to look at at times, but also tough to look away. It’s engrossing, and also quite gross. I’m going to check out the movie, but this has gotta be rough to see on screen.<br /><br />EDIT: I just watched the film, and want to say to anyone who may have seen it and not read the book, that they are very different. Despite Smith doing the screenplay, the book plays out much, much differently and is about 100x more dark and brutal. Worth the read even if you’ve seen the movie.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15028346629580205005" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

